  "decision_conditions": [
    "Flood Risk and Absence of Acceptable Flood Risk Assessment (FRA) The proposal fails to demonstrate, through an acceptable Flood Risk Assessment (FRA) and Evacuation Plan, that future occupants would be safe in the event of surface water flooding. The absence of confirmed Finished Floor Levels (FFL) above the modelled flood depth and lack of a \"Very Low Hazard\" flood evacuation route raises unresolved flood risk concerns. In accordance with the National Planning Policy Framework (2024) and Policies SI12 and SI13 of the London Plan, as well as Local Plan Policies CP28 and DMD61, the development does not adequately mitigate flood risks and therefore cannot be supported.",
    "Heritage Impact and Harm to the Enfield Town Conservation Area the proposed development, including the removal of a historic chimney and the addition of rear and side extensions, fails to preserve or enhance the special architectural and historic character of the Enfield Town Conservation Area. The scale, massing, and design of the extensions introduce visual harm and erode the distinctive rhythm of the built environment, contrary to Section 72(1) of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990, London Plan Policy HC1, Enfield Core Strategy Policies CP30 and CP31, and Development Management Document Policies DMD37 and DMD44. The identified \"less-than-substantial harm\" to the designated heritage asset is not outweighed by the public benefits of the scheme, and as such, the proposal is unacceptable in heritage terms.",
    "Tree Protection and Insufficient Arboricultural Evidence The proposal fails to provide adequate arboricultural assessments, including an Arboricultural Implication Assessment (AIA) in accordance with BS 5837:2012, to justify the impact on trees within and adjacent to the site. The proposed fencing and garden layout would compromise the conservation area's green infrastructure, failing to safeguard trees of townscape and ecological value. The absence of detailed mitigation measures results in non-compliance with London Plan Policy G7, Core Policy CP36, and Development Management Document Policy DMD80."
  ],
